Umno to highlight PAS’ failures in Kelantanhttp://www.freemalaysiatoday.com/category/...es-in-kelantan/KUALA KRAI: Kelantan Umno will activate its briefing sessions to the people by raising awareness on the failure of the PAS state government in administering Kelantan since 1990.Kelantan Umno liaison committee chairman Mustapa Mohamed said among the issues to be raised with the voters were problems related to land ownership, squatters and the lack of economic opportunities.“The people have given PAS the opportunity to develop Kelantan for the past 27 years, yet there have been no changes.“If at all there were (developments) they were done by the federal government,” he told reporters after a meeting with the committee members of the Kuala Geris Polling District Centre (PDM) in Dabong here today.Present at the event was Kuala Krai Umno division head and Dabong assemblyman Ramzi Ab Rahman.Mustapa said in facing the 14th General Election, Kelantan Umno would boost cooperation with the non-governmental organisations (NGO), especially outside Kelantan, to get closer to the young voters residing outside the state.Mustapa, who is also the international trade and industry minister, said Umno would also intensify programmes to approach the university students so that they would not be easily confused by the slander hurled at BN by the opposition.
